    "content": "nullIdentify Your Users and Manage Access\nTABLE OF CONTENTS\nClose\nClose\nSearch\nSearch\n Identify Your Users and Manage Access\n Who Is Salesforce Identity For?\n Salesforce Identity Licenses\n Multi-Factor Authentication\n Single Sign-On\n Identity Connect\n Custom Login Flows\n Login Access\n Manage User Passwords\n Lightning Login for Password-Free Logins\n Certificate-Based Authentication\n Connected Apps\n External Client Apps\n Set Up External Client Apps Permissions\n Create a Local External Client App\n Packageable External Client Apps\n Enable or Disable External Client App Plugins\n OAuth Client Credentials Rotation for External Client Apps\n Rotate OAuth Client Credentials\n OAuth Flow Configuration\n Manage External Client Apps\n External Client Apps Creation with Metadata API\n Authorize Apps with OAuth\n App Launcher\n Manage API Access\n Manage Salesforce User Identities with SCIM\n Salesforce Customer Identity\n Monitor Access to Your Salesforce Orgs and Experience Cloud Sites\n\nYou are here:\n\nSALESFORCE HELP\nDOCS\nIDENTIFY YOUR USERS AND MANAGE ACCESS\nRotate OAuth Client Credentials\n\nKeep your external client apps secure by periodically changing your consumer secret. To rotate credentials, you can provide consumer key or secret values or these values can be generated.\n\nREQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS\nAvailable in: Lightning Experience\nAvailable in: Professional, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions\n\n\nUSER PERMISSIONS\nNEEDED\nTo rotate OAuth client credentials\tCreate, edit, and delete External Client Apps\n\nExternal client apps support changing the consumer key or consumer secret individually or changing both at the same time.\n\nNOTE Immediately after you apply the new consumer details, you can experience up to 10 minutes of unstable behavior as the changes are propagated to the external client app and its integrations. During this time, the old and new consumer details work intermittently. After this 10-minute period, the new consumer details replace the previous values and only the new consumer details work.\nFrom Setup, in the Quick Find box, enter External Client Apps Manager, and then select External Client Apps Manager.\nFrom the actions dropdown list, select Edit Settings for the external client app in need of credential rotation.\nExpand the OAuth Settings section, and then select Consumer Key and Secret.\nYou’re prompted to verify your identity using one of your registered methods. You can view the consumer details page for up to 5 minutes before you’re prompted to verify your identity again.\nTo generate new values for the consumer key and consumer secret, under Staged Consumer Details, click Generate.\nEach time you generate staged values for the consumer key and secret, you overwrite the existing staged values. You can generate new staged values at any time. Staged values aren’t valid until you apply them.\nShare the staged consumer details with your external client app admins and integrations.\nWARNING You can’t revert this change. All existing access and refresh tokens associated with the connected app are revoked when you apply the new consumer details.\nWhen you’re ready to use the staged consumer details, click Apply.\nClick Apply again to accept the warning.\nDID THIS ARTICLE SOLVE YOUR ISSUE?\nLet us know so we can improve!\nYes\nNo\n ",
